snippet.textDisplay:
They do not sing for the king of the earth, they sing for the king of heaven.... Divine.... Soulful.... So beautiful..... one gets transported to a different state of being. True heir of Nusrat Saab. For some reason, I liked this version even more than that of the great Nusrat Saab. Hearing Amjad Sabri saab for the first time - a distinctive voice.

Do not want to bring politics in between - but goes to show that it is all one nation - whether we choose to call it Pakistan or India, people, culture, way of life - everything is the same.

And as the song says, after this short sojourn, we all merge into the divine..... Why the differences now in this short span of life in this earth?
